    "Background": {
      "text": "According to Crimes and Criminal Procedure, Title 18 United States Code (USC) § 2332a, a Weapon of Mass Destruction (WMD) is “any destructive device defined in § 921” (2006). These weapons include any explosive, incendiary, poison gas, bomb, grenade, rocket having a propellant charge of more than four ounces, missile having an explosive or incendiary charge of more than one-quarter ounce, mine, or device similar to the above.\n[1]\nChildren at increased risk to WMD\nIncreased respiratory rate (minute ventilation)\nHeavier chemicals like SARIN will accumulate at a level where children are exposed to\nGreater surface area to volume ratio\nSmall fluid reserves and higher metabolic rates\nDehydration\nIncreased toxicity from same exposure in an adult\n[2]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
